items.label: Introduction to Physical AI & Humanoid Robotics

ch1_1_introduction_to_physical_ai.title: Chapter 1.1 - Introduction to Physical AI
ch1_1_introduction_to_physical_ai.description: Physical AI represents the intersection of artificial intelligence and the physical world. Unlike traditional AI systems that operate purely in digital domains, Physical AI systems must interact with, understand, and manipulate real-world objects and environments.

ch1_2_sensing_and_perception.title: Chapter 1.2 - Sensing and Perception
ch1_2_sensing_and_perception.description: Sensing and perception form the foundation of Physical AI systems. These systems must accurately interpret sensory data to understand and interact with their environment.

ch1_3_actuation_and_control.title: Chapter 1.3 - Actuation and Control
ch1_3_actuation_and_control.description: Actuation and control systems enable Physical AI systems to interact with the physical world through precise movement and manipulation.

ch2_1_humanoid_robot_design.title: Chapter 2.1 - Humanoid Robot Design
ch2_1_humanoid_robot_design.description: Humanoid robot design involves creating mechanical systems that mimic human form and functionality while achieving specific tasks.

ch2_2_locomotion_and_balance.title: Chapter 2.2 - Locomotion and Balance
ch2_2_locomotion_and_balance.description: Locomotion and balance are fundamental capabilities for humanoid robots, enabling them to move and maintain stability in various environments.

ch2_3_human_robot_interaction.title: Chapter 2.3 - Human-Robot Interaction
ch2_3_human_robot_interaction.description: Human-Robot Interaction (HRI) focuses on how humans and humanoid robots can effectively communicate and collaborate.

ch3_1_industrial_applications.title: Chapter 3.1 - Industrial Applications
ch3_1_industrial_applications.description: Physical AI and humanoid robotics are revolutionizing industrial processes with advanced automation and human-robot collaboration.

ch3_2_service_robotics.title: Chapter 3.2 - Service Robotics
ch3_2_service_robotics.description: Service robotics encompasses humanoid robots designed to assist humans in various service-oriented tasks, from healthcare to hospitality.

ch3_3_future_directions.title: Chapter 3.3 - Future Directions
ch3_3_future_directions.description: This chapter explores emerging trends, research directions, and future possibilities in Physical AI and Humanoid Robotics.

intro.title: Introduction to Physical AI & Humanoid Robotics
intro.description: Welcome to the comprehensive guide on Physical AI and Humanoid Robotics. This textbook covers the fundamental concepts, advanced techniques, and practical applications of artificial intelligence in physical systems and humanoid robots.

part1_fundamentals.title: Part 1 - Fundamentals of Physical AI
part1_fundamentals.description: This part covers the fundamental concepts of Physical AI - artificial intelligence systems that interact with and operate in the physical world.

part2_humanoid_robots.title: Part 2 - Humanoid Robotics
part2_humanoid_robots.description: Humanoid robotics focuses on the design, development, and control of robots that resemble human form and behavior.

part3_advanced_applications.title: Part 3 - Advanced Applications
part3_advanced_applications.description: This part explores advanced applications of Physical AI and Humanoid Robotics in real-world scenarios.
